else if (command.startsWith("sendqz")) {
	int range = Integer.parseInt(command.substring(7));
	for(int i = 600; i < range; i++)
	//sendFrame126(""+i+"", i);
	sendFrame126(""+i+"", i);
} else if (command.startsWith("sendzq2")) {
	int range1 = Integer.parseInt(command.substring(8,11));
	int range2 = Integer.parseInt(command.substring(12));
	for(int i = range1; i < range2; i++)
	sendFrame126(""+i+"", i);

::sendqz 700 will check all numbers from 600 - 700 and make em show the number
::sendqz 15000 will check all numbers from 600 - 15000 and make em show the number

or use sendzq2

::sendzq2 0001 12 will check all numbers from 1 to 12 and make em show the number (make sure to use 000 if your number is short cuz of the substring)
